Sentencas: CGO-CuO composites are promising anode materials for low and intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT/IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: CGO20-CuO composites synthesized by the combustion method and characterized by H2-TPR

Sentencas: In this work, several CGO-CuO (65:35; 50:50 y 35:65 mol/mol%) composites by urea combustion synthesis yielding to fine reactive powders at low temperatures were prepared.
Titulo: CGO20-CuO composites synthesized by the combustion method and characterized by H2-TPR

Sentencas: The resulting powder composites were characterized using X-ray diffraction (XRD), N-2 adsorption-desorption (BET) and scanning electron microscopy-energy disperse X-ray (SEM-EDS).
Titulo: CGO20-CuO composites synthesized by the combustion method and characterized by H2-TPR

Sentencas: Additionally, hydrogen temperature programmed reduction (H-2-TPR) tests were carried out, in order to elucidate reducibility of the powders.
Titulo: CGO20-CuO composites synthesized by the combustion method and characterized by H2-TPR

Sentencas: H-2-TPR tests exhibited two primary reduction peaks, which correspond to the following stages: the first one (150-350 degrees C) can be ascribed to the reduction of CuO species into metallic Cu; while the second one (750-900 degrees C) can be ascribed to the bulk Ce4+ -> Ce3+ reduction process of the support (CGO).
Titulo: CGO20-CuO composites synthesized by the combustion method and characterized by H2-TPR

Sentencas: Further, after H-2-TPR reduction of the asprepared CGO-CuO compositions, powders exhibit the presence of metallic Cu and the fluorite CGO solid solution that remains stable whereas any CuO is no longer noticed.
Titulo: CGO20-CuO composites synthesized by the combustion method and characterized by H2-TPR
